    <stitle>VT-365 Diesel Engine Diagnostics (2002) - HARD START AND NO START DIAGNOSTICS - Test Procedures - Engine
        Oil
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Engine Oil</title>
        <figure id="f2400514" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figD31/D3157.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
        </figure>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Purpose</emph>
        </para>
        <para>To determine if crankcase oil level and oil quality are correct to ensure operation of the Injection
            Control Pressure (ICP) system
        </para>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Tools</emph>
        </para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>None</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To avoid serious personal injury, possible death, or damage to the engine or vehicle, read all
                    safety instructions in the foreword of this manual. Follow all warnings, cautions, and notes.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Procedure</emph>
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Park vehicle on level ground.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check oil level with oil level gauge.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Never check the oil level with the engine running or immediately after engine shutdown as an
                        inaccurate reading will be obtained. Allow 15 minute drain down time.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If the oil level is too low, the fuel injectors will not work correctly. If the oil level is
                        above full, the engine has been incorrectly serviced, fuel is in the oil, or coolant is in the
                        oil.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect oil for color and odor.</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>A milky white mix indicates coolant contamination.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Does oil have a diesel fuel odor?</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check engine service records for correct oil grade and viscosity for ambient operating
                temperatures.
                <emph type="bold">Do not use 15W-40 oil below -6.7&#176;C (20&#176;F)</emph>. Long oil drain intervals
                can increase oil viscosity; thicker oil will make engine cranking and starting more difficult below
                freezing temperatures. See Engine Lubrication Requirements in the VT 365 Engine Operation and
                Maintenance Manual. Confirm that oil meets correct API specifications.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Possible Causes</emph>
        </para>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Low oil level</emph>
        </para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>Oil leak</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Oil consumption</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Incorrect servicing</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">High oil level</emph>
        </para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>Incorrect servicing</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Fuel in oil</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Coolant in oil</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Incorrect oil level gauge</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Coolant in oil</emph>
        </para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>Cylinder head gasket leak</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Defective cup plug in cylinder head</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Injector sleeve leak</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Glow plug sleeve leak</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Front cover gasket leak</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Defective oil cooler bundle or O-ring</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Front cover, cylinder head, or crankcase porosity</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Accessory leak (water cooled air compressor)</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Fuel in oil</emph>:
        </para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>Injector O-ring leak</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Cylinder head porosity</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
